properties.headline: Australia Day in Sydney - Tuesday 26 January - CIRCULAR QUAY George Street, Hickson Road
properties.publicTransport: Ferries are not running to or from Circular Quay while an exclusion zone is in effect on the harbour. F3 Parramatta River and F1 Manly ferries are using Barangaroo wharf instead. Route 208 buses are diverting via Wynyard. Visit transportnsw.info for details.

arrangementAttachments.displayName: Australia Day 2021 - Road closures & Clearways map
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Australia Day 2021 - Road closures & Clearways map

properties.otherAdvice:
Roads around Circular Quay and The Rocks are closed for Australia Day events around the harbour.

The Circular Quay foreshore area is closed to the general public from 5pm with access permitted only for those with a venue booking or a ticket to Australia Day Live concert or viewing area. Visit australiaday.com.au for details.

*THE CAHILL EXPRESSWAY IS NOW CLOSED IN BOTH DIRECTIONS*

Key road closure timings:

  • *CLOSED* From 4am to midnight: roads in Circular Quay and The Rocks including sections of Alfred St, Argyle St, Circular Quay West, Essex St and George St.
  • *CLOSED* From 7am to midnight: Hickson Rd from George St to Pottinger St in The Rocks.
  • *NOW CLOSED* From 7.30pm to 10.30pm: the Cahill Expressway lanes 7 and 8 southbound and lane 4 on the Harbour Bridge is closed as well as both directions of the Cahill Expressway Circular Quay Overpass. Roads in Circular Quay north of Bridge St are also closed including sections of Albert St, Alfred St, Essex St, George St, Loftus St, Phillip St and Young St.

The speed limit on the Harbour Bridge will be reduced to 40km/h from 8pm to 9.30pm.

The Cahill Expressway overpass walkway is closed from 5pm to 9:30pm. The Sydney Harbour Bridge Walkway and Cycleway remains open.

Special event clearways are in effect on various roads in Circular Quay and The Rocks from 3am until midnight and on various roads between Circular Quay and Martin Place from 5pm until 10.30pm.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even to local residents and businesses with parking permits and RMS Mobility Scheme permit holders. Check signs carefully on the day and the night before, as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed call 132 701 to find its new location.

properties.displayName: Australia Day in Sydney - Tuesday 26 January

properties.headline: A-League - Sunday 31 January - GOSFORD Dane Drive between Central Coast Highway AND Donnison Street
properties.otherAdvice:
A-League: Central Coast Mariners v Wellington Phoenix from 4:05pm to approx 6pm. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on roads approaching the stadium including Central Coast Hwy, Pacific Hwy, Brisbane Water Dr, Donnison St and Mann St as fans travel to and from the event.

Dane Dr will be closed between the Central Coast Hwy and Donnison St from 3pm and will reopen when crowds have cleared the area.

Motorists should allow extra travel time and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on roads in the area.

properties.headline: A-League - Saturday 30 January - LEUMEAH Pembroke Road and Rose Payten Drive approaching Campbelltown Sports Stadium
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
A-League: Macarthur FC v Sydney FC from 7:10pm to approx 9pm at Campbelltown Sports Stadium. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Pembroke Rd, Rose Payten Dr, Leumeah Rd, Airds Rd, Plough Inn Rd and Campbelltown Rd as soccer fans travel to the game.

Motorists should allow additional travel time and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on roads between the station and stadium.

roads.mainStreet: Pembroke Road and Rose Payten Drive

properties.headline: A-League - Friday 29 January - PARRAMATTA O'Connell Street at Victoria Road
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
A-League: Western Sydney Wanderers v Newcastle Jets at Bankwest Stadium from 7:05pm until 9pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on O'Connell St, Parramatta Rd, Church St, Victoria Rd and James Ruse Dr as fans travel to the stadium during Friday evening peak. Motorists should plan to arrive early and allow extra travel time.

Roads may close prior to full-time to allow crowds to safely leave the area including sections of O’Connell St, Victoria Rd and Ross St.

properties.headline: Australia Day at Dee Why - Tuesday 26 January - DEE WHY The Strand between Dee Why Parade AND Oaks Avenue
properties.publicTransport: Buses will be diverting around The Strand. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures and special event clearways will be in place to accommodate various events in Dee Why on Australia Day. 

Road closures will be in place from 12pm midday Monday 25 January until 6am Wednesday 27 January on The Strand between Dee Why Pde and Oaks Ave and on Howard Ave between Clyde Ave and The Strand.

Resident access to Howard Ave will be maintained via Clyde Rd throughout the closure period.

Special event clearways will also be in effect from 12pm midday on Monday to 6am on Wednesday along The Strand between Dee Why Pde and Oaks Ave.

 Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

properties.headline: Sun Run - Saturday 6 February - DEE WHY, CURL CURL, FRESHWATER, QUEENSCLIFF, MANLY The Strand, Griffin Road, North Steyne & South Steyne
properties.publicTransport: Some buses will divert while roads are closed. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
The annual 10km Sun Run will start at 6:15am from The Strand in Dee Why and finish by 11am at South Steyne in Manly. Road closures, parking restrictions and changed traffic conditions will be in effect.

Road closures:

  • Dee Why - 3.30am to 9am: sections of Howard Ave, The Strand and Dee Why Pde. Crossover maintained on Oaks Ave at The Strand eastbound from 5:15am-7:15am, westbound from 6am-7:15am.
  • Curl Curl to Freshwater - 5:30am to 9am: Griffin Rd, Pitt Rd, Abbott Rd, Carrington Pde and local surrounding roads will be closed. Crossover maintained on Griffin Rd at Pacific Pde in both directions 6am-7.30am, and on Playfair Rd at Pitt Rd in both directions from 6am-8am
  • Queenscliff - 5.30am to 10am: sections of Undercliff Rd, Dalley St, Greycliffe St, Queenscliff Rd, Dowling St, Lumsdaine Dr and surrounding local roads. Crossover maintained on Crowd Rd between Dowling St and Cavill St exit only from 5:30am-6:15am and 9am-10am only.
  • Manly - 3.30am to 9:30am: sections of North Steyne, Raglan St, Collingwood St and other local roads. Managed access for Cameron Ave residents from 5.30am-9am.
  • Manly - 3.30am to 11am: sections of South Steyne, Wentworth St, Ashburner St and Victoria Pde.

Affected residents are advised to travel before or after the roads are closed as managed access will be limited or restricted. 

Special event clearways will also be in effect from 3:30am until 9am on roads in Dee Why, North Curl Curl, Freshwater, Queenscliff and Manly including sections of Abbott Road, Howard Avenue, The Strand, Evans Street, Crown Road and North Steyne.  

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even to local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.
